race.comment: ELIZABASS (8) resumes and the former Victorian faded out at Doomben at her only run for the Richardson stable last preparation. She's trialled well and is right up to this at best. Maps for a soft run with an in-form jockey aboard. The betting will be key. TORONESS (10) is a stablemate to the top selection and seeks the hat-trick off a CL1 win at Dalby. Wiggins is a positive jockey replacement for the apprentice, and she can't be ruled out. XERRI (1) found one better last time out over 1200m at this track, beaten just a nose into second. In the mix. HUSS ON FIRST (12) did her best work late last time over 1100m at Ipswich, finishing fifth. Can feature.
